Abyss

Challenging the Abyss
Access the abyss by tapping the Abyss button on the world map.


Fight your way through each stratum while you search for the stairs leading deeper and deeper into the abyss!

*Note that it is not possible to call on friends for support in the abyss.
Codes
Codes are rules that may affect both characters and enemies in a stratum.

Each stratum or sub-stratum of the abyss will have its own set of codes, though all quests within a stratum will be bound by the same set.

Codes can restrict which characters you may bring into battle, and may enfeeble your party or enhance your enemies among other effects.
Tap on a code to see the details on its effects.

A stratum's codes will be displayed in the bottom left of the map and on each quest's preparation screen. They may also be reviewed in the pause menu during a quest.

Do note that codes take effect the moment you begin a quest, and codes affecting statuses cannot be removed in battle!
Abyss Modes
On top of codes, different abyss modes may have different requirements.

In the Perfectum mode, you will need to achieve on all of the stratum or sub-stratum's boss quests to unlock the gate to the final boss quest of the stratum.

Clearing a quest to its target score will award a status for that quest.

The characters used to clear a quest to cannot be used in any other boss quests in the same stratum.

It is possible to reset a status by tapping on the cleared quest.

By resetting the quest's status, the characters you used in that quest will no longer be restricted from use in other boss quests on the same stratum.

The quest will need to be cleared to once again, however, if the gate to reach the stratum's final boss has not been unlocked.

Traversing between Strata
Tap the Strata button on the top left of the map to access all strata that you have unlocked.

Receiving Abyss Rewards
Rewards in the abyss are given when certain quests are cleared.

Rewards may be reviewed and claimed from the Rewards window.
Gates
Tap on a gate in any of the strata to display the requirements for unlocking that gate.
